The countdown to the British royal wedding is on, and just because you are more than 9,000km away, it doesn't mean you can't get involved. Prince Harry and Meghan Markle are set to marry on May 19 at Windsor Castle, but there are plenty of ways you can show your support for the happy couple. From commemorativee royal wedding mugs to life-size cutouts of the bride and groom, we've found some of the weirdest, wackiest and most wonderful royal wedding memorabilia you can buy. Below, 21 royal wedding souvenirs to commemorate Harry and Meghan's big day: HuffPost may receive a share from purchases made via links on this page.